{"lemma":"سَعادَة","slug":"سَعادَة","root":"س.ع.د","root_slug":"س-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19788"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَعِدَ (saʕida) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"happiness, gladness","examples":[{"text":"السَّعَادَةُ تَغْمُرُنِي.","english":"Happiness overwhelms me."},{"text":"a. 605, al-Nābighah al-Dhubiyānī\nوَٱلرِّفْقُ يُمْنٌ، وَٱلأَنَاةُ سَعَادَةٌ / فَٱسْتَأْنِ فِي رِفْقٍ تُلَاقِ نَجَاحَا\nwar-rifqu yumnun, wal-ʔanātu saʕādatun / fastaʔni fī rifqin tulāqi najāḥā","english":"Gentleness is a blessing; abiding is happiness. / So abide gently to find success."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"luck, good fortune"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bliss"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prosperity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"highness, majesty (title)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a surname"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of سَعِدَ (saʕida, “to be happy, to be lucky”)."},"ipa":["/sa.ʕaː.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19788","headword_ar":"سَعَادَةٌ","root":"sEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEida","text_ar":"سَعِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, TA) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suEida","text_ar":"سُعِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or a simple subst., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prosperity, good fortune, happiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"felicity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAwapN","text_ar":"شَقَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, * K;) with respect to religion and with respect to worldly things: (Msb:) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodN","text_ar":"سَعْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a simple subst.:] it is of two kinds;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxoraAwiy~apN","text_ar":"اُخْرَاوِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relation to the world to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dunoyaAwiy~apN","text_ar":"دُنْيَاوِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to the present world"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the latter is of three kinds;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosiy~apN","text_ar":"نَفْسِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to the soul"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaniy~apN","text_ar":"بَدَنِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to the body"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaArijiy~apN","text_ar":"خَارِجِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to external circumstances"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$qw","text_ar":"شقو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also what next follows.]"}],"source_refs":["MA","TA","Msb"]}]}}